Hinduja Seeks Indian Amnesty on Offshore Funds, Telegraph Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-02-22T06:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/hinduja-seeks-indian-amnesty-on-offshore-funds-telegraph-says.html
Srichand Hinduja, an Indian-born
U.K. businessman, urged Indian Finance Minister Pranab Mukherjee
to allow Indians holding funds in offshore bank accounts to
convert them into Indian rupees, charging them 15 percent to 20
percent tax, the  Daily Telegraph  reported, citing the letter.  In a letter to Mukherjee, Hinduja also called for reforms
in the funding of political parties and the lifting of curbs on
foreign direct investment, to boost  India ’s the country’s
attractiveness as an investment location, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 